This paper discusses the h index, which is a measure of research performance commonly used in computer science. The analysis is based on synthetic series of numbers that simulate real series of citations, which suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), or computers and society (cs.CY).
